Finally an example from a totally different domain: developing window-based applications, for example using QtWidgets. We check if two rectangles overlap and if so, move the second one to another place: QRectr1(100,200,15,15);
QRectr2(110,210,20,20);
if(overlaps(r1,r2))
{
assign(r2,200,300,220,320);
}
